  "text": "Grafana's API key authentication and scope enforcement is implemented across multiple layers:\n\n## API Key Validation Middleware\nThe authentication starts in `pkg/services/contexthandler/contexthandler.go` where the `ContextHandler.Middleware` processes each HTTP request by calling `authenticator.Authenticate()`. This middleware initializes the request context and extracts the API key from the Authorization header.\n\n## API Key Authentication Client\nIn `pkg/services/authn/clients/api_key.go`, the `APIKey` client implements the `Authenticate` method which:\n1. Extracts the token from HTTP Authorization header via `getTokenFromRequest()`\n2. Decodes the token using either modern (`satokengen.Decode`) or legacy (`apikeygen.Decode`) format\n3. Retrieves the hashed key and looks up the API key in the database via `apiKeyService.GetAPIKeyByHash()`\n4. Validates the API key using `validateApiKey()` which checks:\n   - Expiration date (`key.Expires <= time.Now().Unix()` returns `errAPIKeyExpired`)\n   - Revocation status (`key.IsRevoked` returns `errAPIKeyRevoked`)\n   - Organization membership (`orgID != key.OrgID` returns `errAPIKeyOrgMismatch`)\n   - Service account association (required for modern keys)\n\n## Service Account Token Generation\nTokens are generated and validated in:\n- `pkg/components/satokengen/tokengen.go`: Generates service account tokens with format `glSERVICE_ID_SECRET_CHECKSUM` using CRC32 checksums\n- `pkg/components/apikeygen/apikeygen.go`: Legacy API key format using base64-encoded JSON\n\nBoth support `Decode()` and hash validation functions.\n\n## Key Expiration Handling\nAPI key expiration is enforced at multiple levels:\n1. In `pkg/services/authn/clients/api_key.go`, the `validateApiKey()` function checks if `*key.Expires <= time.Now().Unix()`\n2. In `pkg/services/apikey/apikeyimpl/xorm_store.go`, the `AddAPIKey()` function sets expiration based on `cmd.SecondsToLive`\n3. In `pkg/services/serviceaccounts/secretscan/service.go`, the `hasExpired()` function checks token expiration before inclusion in secret scanning checks\n\n## Scope and Permission Enforcement\nAfter API key validation, permissions are synced via `pkg/services/authn/authnimpl/sync/rbac_sync.go`:\n1. The `SyncPermissionsHook` is registered as post-auth hook (priority 120)\n2. It calls `fetchPermissions()` which retrieves user permissions from the access control service\n3. Permissions are grouped by action and scope using `accesscontrol.GroupScopesByActionContext()`\n4. The API key client sets `ClientParams{FetchSyncedUser: true, SyncPermissions: true}` to enable permission syncing\n\n## GRPC Authentication\nFor GRPC endpoints, `pkg/services/grpcserver/interceptors/auth.go` provides:\n1. Token extraction from GRPC Authorization header\n2. API key validation via `apiKeyService.GetAPIKeyByHash()`\n3. Service account role verification (must have Admin role)\n4. Permission fetching via access control service\n5. Disabled service account detection\n\n## Revocation and Secret Scanning\nIn `pkg/services/serviceaccounts/secretscan/service.go`:\n1. `CheckTokens()` retrieves active tokens via `filterCheckableTokens()`\n2. Filters out expired tokens (`hasExpired()`) and revoked tokens (`token.IsRevoked`)\n3. Checks token hashes against external secret scanning service\n4. Can automatically revoke leaked tokens via `RevokeServiceAccountToken()`\n\n## Database Operations\nAPI keys are persisted in `pkg/services/apikey/apikeyimpl/xorm_store.go` with operations:\n- `GetAPIKeyByHash()`: Core lookup method used during authentication\n- `GetApiKeyByName()`: Legacy key lookup for old-format keys\n- `GetAllAPIKeys()`: Retrieve organization's API keys\n- `AddAPIKey()`: Create new key with expiration validation\n- `UpdateAPIKeyLastUsedDate()`: Track API key usage\n\n## HTTP Middleware\nIn `pkg/middleware/auth.go`, role-based access control is enforced via:\n- `RoleAuth()`: Middleware checking user's organization role\n- `Auth()`: Middleware enforcing authentication requirements\nThese work with the API key's associated service account role."
